## Defining a New Widget — Template

```twee
:: MyNewWidgets [widget]

<<widget "myAction">><<nobr>>
    <<set _arg1 = $args[0]>>
    <<set _amount = $args[1] || 1>>

    /* validation */
    <<if !_arg1>><<return>><</if>>

    /* logic */
    <<set $someVar += _amount>>

    /* side effects (notifications, events) */
    <<gainStat "confidence" 1>>
<</nobr>><</widget>>    /* ← ALWAYS close both */
```

Widget files must contain `[widget]` in the passage tag bracket. Tweego loads them before normal passages.
